### Explanatory Supplement to the [Wikipedia:Manual of Style](/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style) Guideline

"Wikipedia:Topic" redirects here. For information about topic bans, see [Wikipedia:Banning policy § Topic ban](/Wikipedia:Banning_policy).

This document, a rather exhaustive [explanatory essay](/Wikipedia:Project_namespace), exists to cast further light upon the sacred texts of the [Wikipedia:Manual of Style](/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style) guideline. It's a supplemental tome, if you will, for those who find the initial guidance... insufficient. Or perhaps, for those who merely require the same information presented in slightly different phrasing to finally grasp it.

This page endeavors to provide additional context and elaboration on concepts already touched upon in the page(s) it so graciously supplements. Do not, for a moment, mistake this for one of [Wikipedia's policies or guidelines](/Wikipedia:Policies_and_guidelines) proper; it has not endured the rigorous, often agonizing, process of being [thoroughly vetted by the community](/Wikipedia:PROPOSAL). It’s more of a well-meaning murmur from the sidelines.

#### [Shortcuts](/Wikipedia:Shortcut)

*   WP:BETTER[WP:BETTER](/Wikipedia:BETTER) – Because everyone wants to be better, few actually put in the effort.
*   WP:WBA[WP:WBA](/Wikipedia:WBA) – Another shortcut. Time, it seems, is always of the essence, except when it comes to reading.

### Explanatory Essay About the [Wikipedia:Manual of Style](/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style) Guideline

One would assume the act of [contributing to Wikipedia](/Wikipedia:Contributing_to_Wikipedia) would be intuitive, a natural extension of basic literacy and common sense. One would be wrong, hence the existence of this [Tutorial](/Help:Introduction) and the veritable library of [policies and guidelines](/Wikipedia:Policies_and_guidelines) that govern this digital realm. It's an ecosystem, you see, and like all ecosystems, it requires rules to prevent total collapse.

*   [Editing policy](/Wikipedia:Editing_policy) – The basic tenets of engaging with the text.
*   [Content policies](/Wikipedia:Core_content_policies) – What, precisely, is deemed acceptable within these hallowed digital pages.
*   [Dispute resolution](/Wikipedia:Dispute_resolution) – Because humans.
*   [Simple rule set](/Wikipedia:Simplified_ruleset) – For those who find the full doctrine too daunting. A common affliction.
*   [Simple style manual](/Wikipedia:Simplified_Manual_of_Style) – A lighter version, for the easily overwhelmed.

#### [Introductions](/Help:Getting_started)

The initial steps into this collaborative endeavor are, predictably, signposted. One might wonder why, if the goal is to build an encyclopedia, there's so much *about* the encyclopedia. But then, one observes the general state of things and understands.

